reviews.title: Very bad vegetarian satay
reviews.text: You will only be 65 once, so with mother of 85 and brother and nieces on Monday 1 September 2025 dinner at the Beren near the Oosterhof. It's sweet that there was a card with congratulations. Some people were satisfied with the food, but mothers and I had taken the vegetarian satay and it was downright bad. Both came home feeling sick. It looked like reheated mud from the weekend and the sauce was miserable. It was sweet that there were fireworks on it, but otherwise the service was also in a Monday dip. For a chain that was created a long time ago. Is maintaining good quality important. Otherwise, the Bears will disappear. Really a shame!

reviews.title: Expensive prices! And small how much on your plate.
reviews.text:
Their dishes are really minimal. Very small measured portions and very expensive for what you get. You get a mouse bite when you order sharing spicy crispy chicken for €10!
A sharing loaded frieze is also really bad for€ 8.50. Also a mouse bite.
The bears is a standardized restaurant. Nothing authentic about it. I won't be coming here again.

reviews.title: Nothing special
reviews.text:
In terms of atmosphere, no comments cozy seated. 
The staff were very friendly and helpful. 
As for the food just fine, nothing special only the price quality is far from being found in some dishes. My partner had the Quattro burger 27.50, it was even smaller than a big Mac at the mcdonalds across the street. Again the taste was fine but is outrageous if you pay that price for a burger and are still hungry afterwards.

reviews.title: A night to remember

reviews.text:
We always come to the Bears with great pleasure, it is a nice restaurant and the service friendly. Allergies were well taken into account.

We had a great meal! See you soon!

reviews.title: Dirty pork tenderloin skewer
reviews.text: Fries were limp and cold and the pork tenderloin skewer was way too seasoned. Just not tasty. So no more pork tenderloin skewers there for me. Too bad about this

reviews.title: Bagger restaurant
reviews.text:
What a crappy restaurant, especially the service.
I came here with my husband to celebrate my birthday.
What a disillusionment that was. We had bread with spreads as a starter and chicken satay as a main course. A grumpy guy came to take our order. Normally the main course comes soon after the bread with spreads, but that guy just made us wait. Only after 20 minutes did he come to ask if we wanted the main course. Not normal. So then we had to wait another fifteen minutes until the satay arrived. He slammed the plates on our table and didn't even say enjoy your meal. Well, the satay was okay, the fries were inedible, the coleslaw was in a very small bowl. After 2 bites it was gone. Then for dessert I had the sorbet. There used to be 2 flavors of ice cream scoops with fruits, whipped cream and sevenup, but now it was a big lump of cassis ice cream with whipped cream, which had already collapsed when it came to the table. There was also no garnish, a waffle or anything else, there was supposed to be some kind of crumb on it. and I tasted a total of 2 raspberries. When I asked for an explanation, the grumpy guy said that's how it was nowadays. So that sorbet cost me 9 euros, which wasn't worth it at all. Afterwards, when we went to pay at the cash register, the cashier didn't even ask if we enjoyed it and she didn't say goodbye when we left. Well, I thought I would have a nice birthday, I have never had such a bad experience as at this Beren restaurant. And apparently I'm not the only one, because it was super quiet in the restaurant. Apparently I'm not the only one who is dissatisfied. People, don't go here, especially not to celebrate a birthday.

reviews.title: Unsatisfied costumers
reviews.text: We ordered our food together with fries. The food was gone and our fries had not arrived yet. After we indicated it twice, it was still not there after 30 minutes. We thought the service was poor and asked for the bill. But with complete surprise, the costs of the truffle mayonnaise and sweet potato fries were also on the receipt. We had not received this either. The least you can do is ensure that this is not stated on the receipt if a customer is not satisfied. This is really bad. We pay for an experience and then you experience such an evening. We will never come back here again.

reviews.title: De Beren Delivers to your home
reviews.text:
Do not feel like cooking?
Food failure?
Or just want to eat delicious food?

Then order from De Beren!

As always, this is a delicious meal.
With good quality.
For the first time I ordered the corn on the cob, which is very tasty!

And I took the September special offer with De Beren socks.

The order even arrived a little earlier!

articleContent.title: Your go-to guide for dog-friendly travel

seoInfo.metaDescription: Traveling with your dog has never been easier—or more fun. Cities across the country boast pet-friendly hotels, parks, and activities. With CESAR® brand’s mission to make the world more pet-friendly and Tripadvisor’s top-rated spots, you can plan with confidence. Whether it’s a quick getaway or a bucket-list trip, our guides help you stay, play, and explore with your pup. Grab the leash and go!
From lakeside lounging to ziplining through the Ozarks, Branson’s summer scene is all about embracing the great outdoors.

articleContent.title: 8 of the best wine shops in Paris

seoInfo.metaDescription: The city of lights, love and wine is the perfect place to find some of the best vino in the world. Stop by one of these wine shops in Paris for amazing drinks and food pairings.

articleContent.title: How to eat your way through Greenville, SC

seoInfo.metaDescription: For those who plan their meals before booking a plane ticket, listen up: There is a place where you can immerse yourself in the dining cultures of 34 countries across five continents without leaving a single city limit. Greenville, South Carolina is much more than a restaurant hub—it has enough festivals, food tours, and dinner views to fuel a lifetime of trips. All of this in mind, it’s no wonder the region will be featured on Season 23 of Bravo’s Top Chef, and host the inaugural Michelin Guide American South Ceremony.

articleContent.title: Why Greenville, SC is the perfect mix of adventure and luxury

seoInfo.metaDescription: There are few places that blend luxury and outdoor adventure like Greenville, South Carolina. The days (and mild weather) are made for adrenaline rushes of all types, while the region’s spas, fine dining, and boutique properties serve up luxury experiences that last well into the evening. It’s not hard to dive into a handful of the many treats on offer, and crafting an itinerary that incorporates a little bit of everything is how you’ll find yourself with a Greenville-shaped spot forever in your heart.

Bangkok is an incredible mashup of centuries-old temples and sleek shopping malls that seem to have sprung up overnight. It can be a lot to navigate, especially when neighborhoods—like the ones along the Chao Phraya River—get revamped every few years. Stick with me. As a longtime local, I can show you the Bangkok that I know and love, guiding you to the best spots in this always buzzing city.

articleContent.title: 5 national parks that put accessibility first

seoInfo.metaDescription: Wheelchair rentals, accessible trails, Braille-ready park maps, and so much more.

They say two is better than one—and in Ixtapa-Zihuatanejo, that couldn’t be more true. Ixtapa is modern and vibrant, with luxury resorts, breathtaking views, and settings surrounded by lush tropical nature. Zihuatanejo, a Pueblo Mágico, offers cobblestone streets, deep-rooted traditions, and a laid-back coastal vibe. Together, they deliver a travel experience that’s as diverse as it is authentic—earning Ixtapa-Zihuatanejo its place among Mexico’s top beach destinations.

articleContent.title: 10 oldest pubs in England and what to order at each

seoInfo.metaDescription: A trip to England isn’t complete without going to the pub. Here are 10 old English pubs to visit and the stories behind them.

reviews.title: Superlekkere Saté
reviews.text:
Als wij moe zijn.
En geen zin hebben om te koken.
Maar wél zin in lekker eten.
Dan bestellen wij bij De Beren!!!

Binnen no-time staat de bezorger voor de deur met een grote doos vol heerlijk eten. Alles netjes apart verpakt én warm!

Onze lievelingskeuze is de varkenssaté, zó lekker!!!
